@Alex-302 
@Sergey-Lyapin 
@AdamWr 
@zloyden 
@BlazDT 

I can't believe after years of reporting pages, that my reports are just getting closed, like I am unaware of what I am doing, instead of investigating (together). It also take my time, to check a page, point to an issue and thats the result. I feel pranked.
Why my reports stay closed when I report that there is still an issue? Why I need to escalate several times to get reports serious? (especially for the big pages like Google, YouTube etc.)

Instagram? I don't care and I don't use it. F* Zuckerberg. I report things to make the internet better and people enjoy AdGuard, because I like it. It's up to you, if you prefer that users delete AdGuard, because it breaks major pages.
I have even linked to another ticket where the same issue existed.

The TOTP 'breaking' rule is: `instagram.com#$?#body > div[role="presentation"]:has(> div[role="dialog"] a[href="/legal/cookies/"]) { display: none!important; }`
After disable the rule and manually deny Cookies, TOTP is working. In desktop view, a autoclicking rule exist. TOTP works. (see old ticket)

And here is the video if you still can't believe....


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6276915/176117681-f2a9132f-ee8d-4657-921d-e2bfd5b346d4.mp4



Feel free to close the ticket just again or take the chance. I don't care. I won't reopen.

And btw. believe it or not, but the Smartbanner is real. I don't have the time to Photoshop a Smartbanner and foul you.

@AdamWr 

I can confirm, the Smartbanner Fix also works fine. Thank you for taking things serious.


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6276915/176136698-930750f1-b886-40c1-a8d9-b674046d354c.mp4
